Preheat the oven to 200°C. Pop the @British honey mustard sausages{4} onto a #baking tray{}, drizzle with a little @oil{} then roast on the top shelf of the oven until golden and cooked, ~{20%minutes}, turn halfway through. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat, the sausages are cooked when no longer pink in the middle. Once cooked, chop the sausages up into small, bite-sized, chunks (be careful, they're hot!).

Meanwhile, bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with a pinch of @salt{} in preparation for the potatoes. Chop the @potatoes{450}(chopped into 2cm chunks) (no need to peel). Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{2}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced). Trim the @carrot{1}(trimmed and thinly sliced into rounds), then thinly slice into rounds. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1} (stalks and all). Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}(grated).

When the water is boiling, add the potatoes to the saucepan and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-20%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} then return to the pan off the heat. Add the @wholegrain mustard{1/2%tsp}, cheese and a splash of @milk{} (if you have it!). Mash until you have a smooth consistency and season to taste with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

In the meantime, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} over medium-high heat. Once hot, add the carrot and red onion. Cook until the carrot is tender and the onion is starting to colour, ~{8-10%minutes}, stirring regularly. Once softened, add the @plain flour{8%g} and @tomato puree{30%g} into the pan. Cook, stirring, for ~{1-2%minutes}, then pour in the @water{250%ml}. Add the @red wine stock paste{4%g}, stirring to dissolve.

Bring the sauce to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until nicely thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from the heat and mix in the sausage pieces and half the parsley. Transfer the filling into an #ovenproof dish{} (keep the pan). Spread the mash over the filling using the back of a #fork{} and pop on the top shelf of the oven to cook until golden and bubbly, ~{10-15%minutes}. In the meantime, rinse out the pan you used for the filling.

Return the pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}. Once hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{60%g}. Stir-fry until golden all over, ~{1-2%minutes}, then add the @shredded Savoy cabbage{100%g} and a splash of @water{} to the pan. Continue to fry, stirring regularly, until the cabbage is tender, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in the remaining parsley, taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Once the pie is out of the oven, serve onto large plates with the cabbage on the side. Enjoy!